\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 Many comments noted frequently mentioned the writers good health and how living under field conditions
 in Africa have immunized them against common ills. The precautions against malaria are thought to be disagreeable but the benefits compensates the individual distaste. There is an indication that there is a contagious skin disease prevalent in this area.
 About 98% of all comments on health are favorable. The following were noted:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"Very soon we have to start malarial precautions which means sleeping under nets and taking Adabrine twice a week until November. Hate to think of it but guess it's better t
han getting the disease, yes? We have now the transportation to take us to the beach several times a week and swimming is fine I have been told."--40th Station Hospital.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "The whole building is set aside for contagious diseases except this one room. Mos
t of the patients have Scages Dorsalis, a very contagious skin disease, but I haven't caught it yet."--10th Field Hospital.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "We have been cold, hungry, homesick, dirty and even had bedbugs."-
52nd Station Hospital.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "Yesterday finished a concrete fl
oor for mess kitchen to keep rats away rats larger than sewer type in city."--Co. C, 242nd QM Battalion.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15421430 2. MALL}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 Mail service to some units continues to be misdirected and delayed; it appears many writers blame the postal system in the States fo
r this condition. It is noted that mail within North Africa is also delayed unnecessarily. The processing of V-mail in this theater
 has increased the volume of mail handled, writers are trying out the system for the 1st time. The receipt of micro-film from
 the States is looked upon as a means of receiving mail with more regularity. About 70% of all comments on mail service has been unfavorable. The following were noted:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"It is a crime the way New York is horsing the mail of the 5th Base Post Office aro
und. Just after I sent you a V-mail letter today telling you I received your letters of March 19, 20, 23, 25, 27, and 29 I received from England your letters properly addressed to me over here, dated March 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, and 9. Also one from \'85
 dated March 
8. No wonder I didn't get any mail from you all during March to speak of and I was at a loss to understand the reason. It is no longer funny. We have been over here long enough for them to know where we are and to ship the mail correctly. My case is not t
he only one being sent in error over here but many others."-5th Base Post Office.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"I would like to know what they do with the mail when it takes so long for it to get here. Perhaps it is put into storage until they get enough to send over in a big bunch
. I don't know, but I do now know that all of this propaganda that you read about the efficient mail service that they have to the troops overseas is a lot of talk and does not belong to reality."--505th C.A.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"Your letter of January 8 reached me yesterday-a mere 96 days in transit. It had been to good old U.S.A. I have wondered what you were doing and have asked about you many times but no one knew about it."--Hq. Fifth Army.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "Have just learned that our
 mail has been misdirected to an area some 300 miles away which accounts for lack of mail for last few days. Hope all this mail is properly redirected."-10th Field Hospital.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "I think I've written about two hundred letters since I left the States and I 
received about six."--509th Parachute Regt.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"Sure have missed hearing from you. Just hope our mail catch up with us before long so far we haven't received any mail for 3 months."--APO 520.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "The mail man just now brought me your letters of Feb. 1st 
and 22nd. Rather late eh? Of course I had already received those of Mar. 1st, 8th, and 29th-so know you were O.K."--12th AFSC.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"I wrote a letter to the chief nurse of another station hospital 2 hours from here and it took her 8 days to get it so you can see what the mail situation is."--32nd Station Hospital.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 
"Today I received your letter dated March 22 and I really couldn't understand what happened because I've been used to reading mail that was two or three months old. So imagine my surprise when 
all of a sudden out of a clear sky the mail orderly hands me four letters. They all are late letters from the 9th of March to the22nd."--Hqs. Det. Fifth Army Engineer Training Center.
