Training has accelerated in this area during the past few weeks. It has been noted that complaints against strenuous training
 has lessened. Many realize what they lacked and are trying to pass this information back to military personnel in the States. Enlisted personnel are being trained to take over hospital duties, particularly for work in the G.O. Wards, surprise is usually 
expressed at their adaptability in replacing the nurses. About 75% of all comments on training emphasize the necessity of training and point out faults that have been found. The following were noted:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "We have in this action trained a group of troops wh
o are now well trained combat units. There are still many things which must be stressed. Communications in combat are vital. The communication must be up to the minute. The tempo of modern combat is so fast that unless your communication can keep up with 
t
he action. The leaders are fighting blind. Leader must do a leader job, planning and directing. They must not become involved in small details, such as acting as telephone orderly, or company clerk. Be sure that the men who are going to execute your plan,
 understand it. Make sure your instructions are clear and complete. Have them repeat it back to you. You will be surprised how much misunderstanding there is."--Hq. 5th Army.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "I gave you this information before, since then lots happened as you know. Thi
s is not from personal experience, as the Lord knows, so far I have none, but from reading and hearing. If I had to train an outfit I would stress the following: Military courtesy and discipline, they harp on that plenty. Perhaps it has no place in action
,
 but if outfits have it they will react quicker to orders; individual protection, get me in the habit of digging fox holes, at once, and deep enough for protection and let tanks run over them; give men rides in buttoned up tanks, so they know how much the
 
tank crew can see; marksmanship (with all weapons) against tanks and planes; mine laying and removal, use of detectors, neutralizing mines and booby traps; night problems, moving into position at night, use of compass; scouting and patrolling; correct tra
n
smission of orders; endurance of all men and officers, ability to go a mile in 10 minutes with equipment; camouflage, individual and vehicles; road discipline with gas and air alarms; amity of outfit to function several days without much sleep and little 
food and water. These are a few hints that will help you to have a darn good outfit. Above all Colonel get rid of officers and key men who are out of place, don't wait until you go into action, it is then too late."--Hq. Fifth Army.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 "Training over here 
has greater reality, the hours are longer and the work more strenuous. The other day I visited an outfit and talked with the band leader for a while. He said the band in the past hadn't gone through the same strenuous training schedule as the rest of the 
t
roops because in combat they are used as couriers and litter bearers. But reports have come back from the front that soldiers who worked in headquarters and got little physical training and band personnel were suffering considerably up at the front. So no
w these band boys are taking their 25 mile hikes and going through the regular training schedule in addition to their playing."--19th Replacement Bn. APO 700.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
