"In recent weeks, we have been having a diet of CPI's which I fear is a joy(?) you have yet to
 experience. There things can be run from your comfortable office in your home town, since they are skeletonized maneuvers without actual troops. However, we don't do things that way. The last one, over the week end, we bounced the entire forward echelon 
about 50 miles over the mountains, and have set up a complete command post in a pine woods." --Hq., VI Corps.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
