"I spent the afternoon out on the rifle range undergoing recruit instructions on the proper method in which to shoot a pistol. You see several 
weeks ago the officer in command of our unit decided we should all shoot the pistol. Well, as usual, I missed the target most of the time and out of a possible two hundred I was successful in making thirty-five. This was so lousy that \'85
 decided I needed so
me recruit instructions, which is what I was doing this afternoon. Since I've at least been shown the correct way to hold and shoot the pistol, I believe I will better my old score by at least one hundred percent the next time I shoot. Would you believe t
hat in the years I've been in the army, I have never had any instructions relative to rifle or pistol procedures? I was able to under
stand the causes of my poor shooting after the schooling, and I think most of my fault in the past has been my ignorance in knowing how to hold the weapon."--Hq. Co., VI Corps.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15421430 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16413026 
