o doubt; eventually I will have no nurses at all and all ward men to run my wards for me. The way they have taken to the care of sick is phenomenal. I would never have believed it had I not seen them work and worked with them. I have the greatest respect 
and admiration for them. They have done a swell job for me and I shall be eternally grateful to them."--12th General Hospital.
