I should like to tell you that we now have a American Radio Station over here, and we get all the programs that we used to hear back home. They also attempt to have them the same time and day that they were on in the States.
 Of course, they are delayed broadcast (on records) but they sure do help a lot. Tonight, being Sunday, we will hear the American Telephone Hour, Jack Benny, and Charlie McCarthy. They also have the regular shows so we can pick just what we want for the e
vening's entertainment." - Det. 12th Weather &renal-on.
