d to provide a rest as a special reward for officers and men. Don't know what I've done to deserve a special reward but anyhow, I got in on the first camp, and felt quite complimented. It started on the 15th and ends either the 19th or 20th. We have nothi
ng to do except swim, play tennis, hike, or just loaf. I spent all day yesterday swimming and sunning myself, and overdid it a bit. I got beautifully sunburned, from the top of my head to the tips of my toes."--Hq. Fifth Army.
