"We find increasing comfort on our radio. We have a government radio and we can get anything that is sent of any kind 
of etheric medium. Our best most popular propaganda is one that comes on every night at 8 p.m. It is devoted to the poor lonely boys in the Dark Continent, Africa. The sponsor is A. Hitler advertising the Third Reich. They specialize in arguments 'why we 
a
re in Africa' on the 'Communist Menace!. All this is interspersed with music calculated to mike us homesick. Every night we gather around and laugh like hell, we are trying to figure out just how we can send a few requests. Too bad that we don't have an A
merican propaganda station we certainly could give some mighty fine answers to Mr. Sehickelgruber and his Heinigang."--438th Sq., 39th Group.
