s and Italians but also our ground forces. I don't know what the trouble is but I have actually had to drive sixty miles to draw rations far my men when I could have been issued the same rations from a ground force dump only a mile or so away. With transp
ortation very scarce, this certainly seems to be a very poor arrangement."--82nd Fighter Control Group.
