 being assigned to anything is becoming quite monotonous and I am growing quite stale on the things that I should be up on in order to perform the work that is expected of me. And to top everything off practically every other thing that they do around her
e is contrary to the things that we were taught and also the rules and regulations of the books. And I am not at all ashamed to say that I am quite fed up on everything. About the only thing that I think we are getting that I like is a lot of physical tra
ining and a lot of road marching. In fact we do 4 miles in 42 minutes. We double time for a half mile and quick time for a mile and so forth until we have completed 4 miles." -.Hq.Co., 6th Bn., 1st Replacement Depot.
