"I can't shape the destines of the world, but I hope that when this mess is over there will be no Germany or no Japan. I only hope that coming gener
ations won't have to send their sons through the hell our boys are going through now. I'm with them and suffer with them, swear and curse with them and will go through hell with them, but it will all be worth it if those who follow us will be
 able to enjoy peace. I also hope our country will always be armed to the teeth so that we will not fail like France did."--183rd Inf., 36th }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid600565 Division}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9251421 .
