the older men in the army, I really think that, unless they are useful technicians, men of that age are of far more value in defense plants. I know that I'm still pretty far away from it, and I find many of the things we have to do pretty tough, physicall
y
 until the army can devise some system where the older men don't have to take part in the strenuous action. I feel that they are serving a better purpose at home. Keeps more beds in the hospitals empty for those that really need care."--286th Signal Compa
ny.
