"One tip I can pass on is when in the open don't open your C ration when the sun shines. We found out the hard way. We would start to eat in the field and first thing over came the Messerschmitt\rquote 
s and raked us with MG fire. Next day we changed locat
ion and the time for chow but same thing we got it again. Finally after a few days I happened to talk with an Air Corps man and he said the lids and cans reflected the rays of the sun and sent up heliograph signals which Jerry waited for--and we got it. N
eedless to say we now open cans up in tents or bend over them and we live that much longer."--QM Section, Base Headquarters, APO 600.
